<br>
this is ripped from a post by one of our guild sk's who is running 7800hp raid buffed in ntov gear. granted he has a sick amount of AA points.<br>
<br>
&quot;I have mainly followed a defensive sequence for my AA so far, with a few offensive ones thrown in here and there. With defensive ones finished, I will be doing offensive ones soon.<br>
ND3, CS3, CA3, PE, and then planar durability, lightning reflexes, innate defense from pop abilities. Along with a few points into stamina when it was lower.<br>
ND3, PE, planar durability were all well worth it for the hps gained. CA was also good. Whether CS3, ID, LR make much of a difference I am not really sure. Mitigation is fairly important now, so I think it does help in PoP.<br>
<br>
Soul Abrasion 3 - The best SK aa really, supposedly the SK equivalent of slay undead 3 I guess, but pallies got ripped off with how few mobs SU3 works on (and its only 20% increase in average damage dealt against them anyway, and is spiky), but maybe they got the better use of it pre-pop.<br>
SU3 increases the lifetap from self imbue lifetap proc buffs by 3 times. With the level 55 buff that makes the proc from 50 lifetap to 150. With the 63 lifetap it makes it from 65 to 195. It's constant, its consistent, it works on all mobs (that arent 100% MR), really nice skill.<br>
<br>
2h Bash - Good skill, tiny DPS increase, but good for interrupting casting. Before PoP it only interrupted up to level 55 mobs, same as regular bash. Now with PoP it interrupts blue con mobs (that arent immune to stun component of stun spells I guess, ie no dragon/giant flagged mobs.. pop giants areng giant flagged so most blue things in pop it works on). Also has the normal ~1 second semi stun to it on mobs it works on, if a mob is running away and then 2h bashed, it will stop still for a second. Also during the time the mob is bash stunned it doesnt attack, though this may not actually decrease damage taken if the mobs swing timer keeps going, they will just attack straight after. I havent looked into this though.<br>
<br>
Spell Casting Fury - Really crappy skill at level 1-2, at level 3 it becomes good. A lot of points for what it is I guess, but with self imbue lifetap procs increased, zevfeers bites, lifetaps, weapon procs etc, its actually quite nice. Also needed to get full effect from HT increasing AAs later.<br>
<br>
Leech Touch - Makes next HT do less damage, but lifetaps. Doesn't stack with any other HT disc or aa, and uses regular HT timer. Kind of weak in a way for most purposes, but an instant 900pt damage/heal can come in handy especially when I know for sure that a heal wont land on me in time. Has probably saved my life in excess of a dozen times while exping, but maybe I just know its there for exp groups so can be more risky with my heals. Raids I have used it a few times as a sort of quick heal for myself if Pooby drops. I can only recall it saving my life maybe once in this situation though.<br>
Later I can increase the ammount this will lifetap for (from 900 to 1500 at the cost of 9 aa I think, a bit steep).<br>
<br>
Super Harm Touch + Unholy Touch - Proper HT upgrader, level 1 UT increases HT base to 1500 base, and auto crits (so always will do 3000 damage with SCF3). Also stacks with HT discipline which further increases the damage by 50% (so to 4500).<br>
Level 2 should be to 2k base (4k always crit, 6k with disc).<br>
Level 3 should be to 3k base (6k always crit, 9k with disc).<br>
These would all be more with focus items.<br>
Unholy Touch &amp; Leech Touch its only one or the other though, if I blow one I can't use either til they reset (60 mins, can get it down more with more AA).<br>
I only have Unholy Touch 1 at the moment, will be working on UT3 next I think. Fast damage is becoming more important with PoP.<br>
<br>
Speed of the Knight, Knights Advantage - Increases number of attacks while using 2h. Worth it for the DPS increase from what I gather, I have level 1 of each but it can wait til after HT. I also hate knight 1h weapons with a passion at the moment, the huge DPS drop is too big for the minimal defensive gain at the moment with the current generation of knight 1h weapons (or lack of them really).<br>
<br>
Thats all of note for SK.. other than Fearless (which I have yet to see an encounter it will be useful on, maybe Aerin'Dar?).. at 12+6 points to get this, seems fairly expensive for something that is never used. I have always expected to see a mob that requires the MT to have this, but haven't seen it yet. I don't have it anyway to comment more, nor do I plan on unless there is a need for it.&quot;<br>
<br>
add all this in with uber instant aggro and the fact he only has 600hp less than our guilds ma means that we should start bitching for a nerf to knights if you guys aren't going to come to the party and back us in our requests for reasonable upgrades<br>
<br>
mewkus<br>
oggietank<br>
<br>
