the ogre part is irrelavant, but the time played is big.  i have experimented with many many weapons combos...<br>
going all the way back to mino axes and stuff...<br>
<br>
my first &quot;magic&quot; weapon was a Brutechopper..(weeee<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )   <br>
<br>
the point here is that not long ago, my guild desided that we would have a big discussion about what weapons do for the tank to control agro.   my point was that if you have fairly speedy weapons with a proc that snares, stuns, nukes, or makes critters mad at you, you WILL hold agro.<br>
<br>
i put this to the test a couple of times...MT'd Treah in PoG with Trochilic's Skean and a Silken Whip of Ensnaring.<br>
we had a couple of SK's there and one was new to the guild and itching to prove how much of a tuff guy he was...he tried to steal agro from me and failed.  i used the same weapon combo in CT where a rogue doing sick DPS couldnt pull the mob off me.<br>
<br>
i have moved onto new weapons...new ideas and stuff, however, the basic idea is that if it makes the mob mad, do it.  Trochilic's Skean may not appear to be that good of a weapon, but if you consider it's stun and minor damage, the thing really does kick butt.   i still carry it, sentimental, i suppose.<br>
<br>
i would also like to say, in my experience, never can a warrior out agro an SK with a 2 handed weapon.  just doesnt seem possible.<br>
<br>
Darvinn Wrathchild<br>
lvl60 big kahuna<br>
