<br>
You, DiedraofXev, just like Goladus, show that when all else fails you have to ignore or modify the meaning of words to fit your conclusion.  In your case, you decided that &quot;not as efficient&quot;, &quot;third choice&quot;, and &quot;a risk vs a known&quot; all mean &quot;useless&quot;.  Hell, you even intimated that useless means something other than useless due to space constraints in a really big book called a dictionary.  <br>
<br>
Here's an aside:<br>
<br>
Did you know there was another book, similar to a dictionary, called a thesaurus, in which words of similar meaning are grouped together for ease of reference, thereby allowing for better definitions of words in the actual dictionary itself?  Roget has a stellar one, I suggest you look into it.  (Don't get the pocket guide, not very big, not the effect I'm looking for).<br>
<br>
Back to my point:<br>
<br>
By showing what wonderful ways (and they are wonderous, these abilities, that the other classes get...the ones that get aggro, that heal folks, that do damage...really neat stuff) folks can work around the flaws in the Warrior class in regards to game mechanics, you have unwittingly described the exact scenario that we have collectively posted about.  The conclusion others are reaching (ok, not you or anyone you know or have ever grouped with, no need to get all indignant) is simply <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>WHY SHOULD THEY BOTHER WORKING AROUND SOMETHING THAT DOESN'T HAVE TO BE WORKED AROUND IF A KNIGHT IS TANKING INSTEAD OF A WARRIOR</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  People (drivers of toons, eaters of Cheetos, drinkers of Code Blue Cherry Super Mountain Pepper Turbo Edition) are lazy.  They do the least that they have to, and they like it that way.  It's part of that efficiency thing (dictionary, anyone?).  This issue here is game mechanics.  How hard is it to push the taunt button every six seconds?  How hard is it to push that same button, if not ever six seconds, then every six seconds while the mob is sticking its boot up someone's ass other than your own?  This is not a player skill thing, but nice way to minimize the problem.  Just because the bat being swung at your head hasn't hit yet doesn't mean it isn't coming.<br>
<br>
Now, this post is brought to you by Reading Comprehension.  If you don't understand the concept, then my post will look like it was written by stuffing a weasel in a burlap sack and banging it repeatedly on the keyboard.<br>
<br>
No weasels were harmed in the making of this post.<br>
<br>
